<subSubSection id="B30C681D0A627AE0189C8A2098762316" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="97214BB6F1F3C0647ECCAAAFAAE6AC13" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C3AB3B35491D5C36647A8B8E2742B709" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">The species epithet, robustum, is of Latin derivation and refers to the very robust cerci of this species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="82239FA3D7735220C54D38C4CF58DF93" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="32ADF3719F07747639FB02081339A53C" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9EBE70B06AA2ADDAD5506BE2356BFCCE" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Among Nearctic species of 
<taxonomicName id="91C6F85A8D27815491AEE86112C10E74" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Allotrichoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Allotrichoma" order="Diptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Allotrichoma</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1CBE9FB0872FFDBA53F46461E2F8FDAD" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Allotrichoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Allotrichoma robustum" order="Diptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustum">Allotrichoma robustum</taxonomicName>
has the most restricted distribution, being thus far known only from the Sierra Mountains in California and Harney County in Oregon.
</paragraph>
